The paper deals with the transmission of status information through a wireless multiaccess channel, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT). The use of a random field and spatial sampling points suggests a systems and control perspective (cs.SY), while the optimization of sampling density is a topic in mathematical optimization (cs.MA). The study of remote estimation error involves numerical analysis (cs.NA), and the use of correlation functions and simulation results suggests a signal processing approach (cs.SP).
